# Redesign Tasks Page to Match Timesheet UI

## Goal Description
Refactor [Tasks.jsx](file:///home/aravinth/Anti%20Gravity/src/pages/Tasks.jsx) to mirror the visual structure of [Timesheet.jsx](file:///home/aravinth/Anti%20Gravity/src/pages/Timesheet.jsx).
- **Layout**: Switch from "Card per Day" to "Single Card containing List of Days".
- **Styling**: Adopt the "Day Header + Left-Bordered List" style from Timesheet.
- **Interactions**: Remove inline logging (verified by "user can only view the tasks"). Keep "Add Task" button.

## Proposed Changes

### [Tasks.jsx](file:///home/aravinth/Anti Gravity/src/pages/Tasks.jsx)

#### 1. Wrapper Structure
- Replace the `space-y-6` container of mapped dates with a single `div className="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden"`.
- Inside, use `div className="divide-y divide-gray-100"`.

#### 2. Day Group Rendering (Map Loop)
- Render each [date](file:///home/aravinth/Anti%20Gravity/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx#272-317) group using the Timesheet style:
    ```jsx
    <div key={date} className="p-6 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
             {/* Date Header */}
             <h3 className="font-bold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
                 <Calendar size={18} className="text-indigo-600" />
                 {...formattedDate...}
             </h3>
             {/* Optional: Summary stats for the day if relevant, similar to Timesheet total hours? Maybe "X Tasks, Y Hours Planned"? */}
             <span className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500">
                 {/* Logic to calc daily hours */} hrs
             </span>
        </div>
        <div className="space-y-2 pl-6 border-l-2 border-gray-100">
             {/* Task Items */}
        </div>
    </div>
    ```

#### 3. Task Item Rendering
- Remove `Play` button and `Inline Log Form`.
- Render task items using Timesheet Entry style:
    ```jsx
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between text-sm">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
             <div className={`w-2 h-2 rounded-full ${status.dot}`}></div>
             <span className={`font-medium ${status.text}`}>{task.task_content}</span>
        </div>
        <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
             {/* Status Badge? Or just ETA? */}
             {task.eta && <span className="font-medium text-gray-900">{task.eta} mins</span>}
             {/* Maybe a completion badge if completed? User wants EXACT like timesheet. Timesheet has "Planned/Unplanned" badge. We can show "Pending/Completed" or nothing. */}
        </div>
    </div>
    ```

